.SH NAME
SVGFilterElement.width \- SVGFilterElement: width property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]width\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]SVGFilterElement\f[R] interface describes the horizontal size of
an SVG filter primitive as a \f[CR]SVGAnimatedLength\f[R].
.PP
It reflects the \f[CR]width\f[R] attribute of the \f[CR]<filter>\f[R]
element.
The attribute is a \f[CR]<length>\f[R] or a \f[CR]<percentage>\f[R]
relative to the width of the filter region.
The default value is \f[CR]100%\f[R].
The property value is a length in user coordinate system units.
.SH VALUE
An \f[CR]SVGAnimatedLength\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] filter = document.querySelector(\[dq]filter\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] horizontalSize = filter.width;
console.log(horizontalSize.baseVal.value); \f[I]// the \[ga]width\[ga] value\f[R]
.EE
